Release manual

Begin with:
* Make sure that all changed are commited to SVN
* grunt test

Labb (release from trunk):
* grunt release (build)
* grunt serve:dist (test)
* rsync --delete -r dist/ fkkorp@k2.spraakdata.gu.se:/var/www/html_sb/korplabb (deploy)

Release candidate
  - Bump the version number in packages.json and app/markup/about.html, commit the changes
  - Merge trunk into korp-current
  - On korp-current:
      > grunt release (build)
      > grunt serve:dist (test)
      > rsync --delete -r dist/ fkkorp@demo.spraakdata.gu.se:/export/htdocs/korprc (deploy)

    Available at: http://demo.spraakdata.gu.se/korprc/

Production (release from korp-current branch):

  For major changes:
    - Tag latest release
    - We should release in the beginning of the week
    - Run release.sh and upload zip to web

  On korp-current:
    > grunt release (buld)
    > grunt serve:dist (test)
    > rsync --delete -r dist/ fkkorp@k2.spraakdata.gu.se:/var/www/html_sb/korp (deploy)

